A ground bone section. 
In generating this sample, a slice of bone is ground down between two plates until it is thin enough for light to shine through it. Bone dust settles in the lacunae, canaliculi and central canal and blocks light; this causes them to appear black in this preparation.
This demonstrates the dense network of canaliculi that ramifies throughout the bone matrix, and permits molecular exchange between the osteocytes in their lacunae and the blood vessels in the central canal.

CC = central canal
L = lacunae
C = canaliculi
O = osteocytes
IL = interstitial lamellae
